***** Unit 4 Introduction *****
In our last unit we move up from two to three dimensions. Now we will have
three main objects of study:
   1. Triple integrals over solid regions of space.
   2. Surface integrals over a 2D surface in space.
   3. Line integrals over a curve in space.
As before, the integrals can be thought of as sums and we will use this idea in
applications and proofs.
We'll see that there are analogs for both forms of Green's theorem. The work
form will become Stokes' theorem and the flux form will become the divergence
theorem (also known as Gauss' theorem). To state these theorems we will need to
learn the 3D versions of div and curl.
